HEADWORD: Pyrolignite
<hw>Py`ro*lig"nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A crude acetate
produced by treating pyroligneous acid with a metal or basic compound;
<as>as, <ex>pyrolignite</ex> of iron (iron liquor)</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyrolignous</ent>⟦br⟧
